=== TASK ===
# Search & Filter Destinations

## Overview
Implement a robust, performant search and filtering experience for Roam Resort destinations. This feature enables guests to discover published destinations via a fast, debounced search box with suggestions, and to refine results by region, style, and keywords. The results are presented on a public Destination Listings (Browse) page with paginated results and clean navigation to Destination Detail pages. A reusable Destination Detail template will render rich, editorial content supplied by hosts, including image galleries, narrative sections, experiences, and a clear CTA to initiate the inquiry flow.

This prompt provides concrete, actionable specifications for frontend, backend, and integration work, including data models, APIs, UI components, accessibility requirements, and acceptance criteria. It enforces runtime safety rules: all code must guard against null/undefined values before array method usage, use data ?? [] for Supabase results, and initialize React state with proper defaults.

## Components to Build
- DestinationSearchBar (Debounced Search with Suggestions)
  - Debounce input with accessible autocomplete suggestions
  - Keyboard navigation (Arrow keys, Enter)
  - Results live-update as user types
  - Accessibility: aria-labels, role="search", proper live regions
- DestinationFiltersPanel
  - Filter by region (multi-select or single-select)
  - Filter by style (multi-select or single-select)
  - Filter by keywords/tacit tags
  - Reset/Apply controls
- DestinationListings (Browse) Page
  - Public page listing published destinations
  - Grid/List responsive cards with image, title, region, style, snippet
  - Client-side sorting options (optional): relevance, newest
  - Pagination / infinite scroll with server-side pagination
  - Click on destination card navigates to DestinationDetail (Reusable Template)
- DestinationCard (UI Card)
  - Visuals: hero image, title, region, style badges, short excerpt
  - Hover: subtle elevation and bronze-gold accent
  - CTA: “View Destination” or similar
- DestinationDetailTemplate (Reusable Template)
  - Editorial narrative sections, large imagery, image gallery, and host-sourced content
  - Experience details with icons/stats
  - In-page CTA to start inquiry flow
  - Consistent typography and editorial layout
- InquiriesCTABar (on Detail)
  - Prominent CTA to begin the inquiry flow
  - Contextual summary (destination name, region)
- API Layer
  - Search and filter endpoint for destinations
  - Detail endpoint for a destination
  - Pagination support
  - Caching layer for common queries (server-side, e.g., in-memory or Redis)
- Data Mipelines
  - Data normalization for destination items
  - Safe access patterns for potential nulls

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks/Tech: React (with hooks), Next.js is acceptable; TypeScript strongly preferred.
- State Management: Local component state for search and filters; consider lightweight context or SWR/React Query for data fetching and caching.
- Debounced Search:
  - Debounce interval: 250–300ms
  - Show suggestions as user types
  - Accessibility: screen-reader friendly
- Filtering UX:
  - Region, style, and keyword tag filters
  - Use accessible controls (checkboxes, pills, or selects)
  - Persist filter state in URL query parameters for shareability and deep linking
- Data Handling & Safety:
  - All arrays guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) and Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - Supabase-esque responses: use data ?? [] for results
  - API responses validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - useState defaults: const [destinations, setDestinations] = useState<Destination[]>([])
- Pagination & Performance:
  - Server-side pagination with page and pageSize query params
  - Prefetch next page when user nears end (infinite scroll) or explicit pagination controls
  - Caching for popular queries (e.g., region+style combinations)
- DestinationCard Component:
  - Responsive grid with 8–12px rounded corners
  - Hover state: slight scale-up and bronze-gold border accent
  - Ensure image lazy-loading and aspect-ratio handling
- DestinationDetailTemplate:
  - Reuse editorial layout across pages, with host-sourced content
  - Rich image gallery with lightbox support (optional)
  - CTA to inquiry flow and host content blocks
- Accessibility:
  - Semantic HTML, alt text for images, proper heading structure
  - Keyboard accessible filters and navigation
- Security:
  - Ensure API calls are protected where necessary (read-only for listings)
  - Validate and sanitize inputs on the client; server-side validation enforces schema

### Backend
- Database: PostgreSQL (with optional Elasticsearch support)
- Data Models:
  - destinations
    - id (UUID)
    - title (text)
    - region (text)
    - styles (text[] or jsonb) -> array of styles
    - tags (text[] or jsonb) -> keywords/tacits
    - description (text)
    - editorial_content (jsonb) or separate sections
    - images (text[] or jsonb) -> URLs
    - published (boolean)
    - created_at, updated_at
  - destination_regions (lookup table) or Enum
  - destination_styles (lookup table) or Enum
  - hosts (for editorial content)
  - inquiry_flow_metadata (optional)
- Full-Text Search:
  - Implement Postgres full-text search on destinations.description, editorial_content.summary, and tags
  - Search endpoint accepts query string and filters; fallback to simple ILIKE if too heavy
- API Endpoints:
  - GET /api/destinations
    - Query params: q (string), region (string|array), style (string|array), tags (string|array), page, pageSize, sort
    - Returns: { data: Destination[], total: number, page, pageSize }
  - GET /api/destinations/{id}
    - Returns: Destination with editorial content and images
- Caching:
  - Cache common query results (by serialized filters) for a short TTL (e.g., 60s) to speed repeated queries
- Validation & Safety:
  - Validate input types; default to safe values if missing
  - Use nullish coalescing for optional fields
- Security:
  - Read-only endpoints for guests; ensure proper authentication gates where necessary for editorial content
  - Use role-based guards per project permissions if integrated with a larger auth system

### Integration
- Data Flow:
  - Frontend calls /api/destinations with current search, filters, and pagination
  - Server runs Postgres search + filters, returns safe data
  - Frontend renders DestinationListings with DestinationCard components
  - Clicking a card navigates to DestinationDetailTemplate with id
  - DestinationDetailTemplate fetches /api/destinations/{id} for full content
- URL State:
  - Reflect search and filters in URL: /destinations?q=beach&region=Caribbean&style=resort&page=1
  - Back/forward navigation preserves state
- Caching Strategy:
  - Client-side: SWR/React Query caches per query key; server side: TTL-based caching for common permutations
- Error Handling:
  - Graceful fallback UI if no results found
  - Loading skeletons and accessible status messages

## User Experience Flow
1) Visitor lands on Destination Listings (Browse) page
2) Debounced search bar provides suggestions and live results as user types
3) User refines results with Region and Style filters and keyword tags
4) Results are paginated or infinitely scrolled; the list updates in real-time
5) User clicks a Destination Card to open Destination Detail (Reusable Template)
6) Destination Detail presents editorial narrative, image gallery, experiences, and host-sourced content
7) Prominent CTA guides user to the inquire flow (authenticate if needed)
8) User proceeds to submission flow or signs in
9) Optional: User can share or bookmark destinations; URL query reflects current state

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details]
- destinations
  - id: UUID
  - title: TEXT
  - region: TEXT
  - styles: TEXT[] (array of styles)
  - tags: TEXT[] (keywords)
  - description: TEXT
  - editorial_content: JSONB (sections, gallery, host notes)
  - images: TEXT[] (image URLs)
  - published: BOOLEAN
  - created_at: TIMESTAMPTZ
  - updated_at: TIMESTAMPTZ
- hosts (optional)
  - id, name, bio, avatar
- inquiries (for later flow)
  - id, destination_id, guest_id, status, created_at, updated_at

API Endpoints: [Routes and methods]
- GET /api/destinations
  - Query: q, region[], style[], tags[], page, pageSize, sort
  - Response: { data: Destination[], total: number, page: number, pageSize: number }
- GET /api/destinations/{id}
  - Response: { id, title, region, styles, tags, description, editorial_content, images, published, created_at, updated_at }
- Optional: GET /api/destinations/search?query=... for specialized search

Security: [Authentication, authorization requirements]
- Destinations listing and detail: public (no auth)
- Inquiries: guest-authenticated flows
- Editorial content: protected by host role for editing; read-only for guests
- API calls should be protected with CSRF/XSRF tokens if using cookie-based auth; prefer JWT or session-based guards depending on system

Validation: [Input validation rules]
- q, region, style, tags: strings or arrays; normalize to arrays
- page, pageSize: integers with sensible bounds (page >= 1, 1 <= pageSize <= 100)
- Ensure all external inputs are sanitized; disallow unnecessary wildcard operations that could degrade performance
- Use safe defaults: page=1, pageSize=20, q=""

Data Handling & Safety (Coding Standards)
- Supabase-like handling in code: use const items = data ?? []
- Guard array operations: (destinations ?? []).map(...)
- React state defaults: const [destinations, setDestinations] = useState<Destination[]>([])
- API response validation: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining for nested API objects: obj?.property?.nested

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Destination search supports debounced input with suggestions and accessible keyboard navigation
- [ ] Filters by region, style, and tags return correct subset of published destinations
- [ ] Results are paginated with accurate total counts; URL reflects current filters and page
- [ ] Destination Listings render responsive cards with correct imagery, metadata, and hover states
- [ ] Destination Detail Template renders editorial content, gallery, experiences, and a prominent inquiry CTA
- [ ] All code paths defensively guard against null/undefined values before array methods
- [ ] Server-side search uses Postgres full-text search or safe ILIKE fallback; caching for common queries implemented
- [ ] UI adheres to the Visual Style guidelines: colors, typography, spacing, and interactive states

